Durando against Mooney. On moving to amend,, a justice’s return tb a writ of certiorari, ana affidavit upon which the writ was founded, or copies thereof, should be produced. S. A. Foot,

moved to amend a Justice’s return to a writ of certiorari.

Lovett, contra,

objected, that neither the return and afhdavit on which the certiorari was founded, nor copies thereof, were produced.

Curia.

The motion piust, for that reason, be denied.

Motion denied.
